		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<a href="spotify.com">Spotify</a> finally came to America and I love it. I've had a <a href="rhapsody.com">Rhapsody</a> account for a year or so. I've liked Rhapsody for its selection of music, but there's no native Mac app (just a web player), the iPhone app is marginal and it's impossible to use your iPhone as a remote control for the player.

Spotify fixes all of those problems except the remote control, but fortunately, someone else did: <a href="http://remoteless.no/">Remoteless</a>. It's a crufty app, but I'm sure it'll get better now that Spotify is in the large US market.  Goodbye Rhapsody.

Best of all, thanks to <a href="http://www.rogueamoeba.com/airfoil/">Airfoil</a> + <a href="http://reemoteapp.com/">Reemote</a>, I can play Spotify throughout the house just like I do with iTunes + Apple's Remote app. So I can listen to any music I want for just $9.99/month. I may never buy another album again. It's a wonderful world we live in.]]></content:encoded>
